The paper discusses a new approach to improve the scalability of static program analysis, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the detection of security bugs, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The approach proposed in the paper involves optimization plans and capturing overlaps and inconsistencies among different properties, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY).
